	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 28th 1:22 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.42]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well I hear that the gnomes have invented a kinda diaper ye pull on under yer clothes to absorb...oh ye said CROWD control sorry:P<br><br>Ok problem one, ye shouldnt have to get that close but you do need to wait till the one ye assisting is actually meleeing the crit, Ive found that if I do an assist while hes running towards group it will target at random sometimes one thats not even being pulled. So wait till he stops and is swinging at crit.<br><br>Problem two part A. chanters at reletivly early age,lvl 20 get AOE mezzes so they dont have to worry bout targeting to mezz, what youll have to do is click on the crits till ye see one that isnt being hit highlighted then cast. Part B. the pet problem is a common occurance and unlike the rest of the pets, we cant command ours so once they agro a crit they go till one or others dead, the only answer Ive found for this is no pet, I dont summon pets for groups anymore unless multiple pulls are never or very rarely a factor. <br><br>My chanters only lvl 24 so there may be better strategies from the more experianced chanters out there. <br>&nbsp;<br>Fiddo Lupineopolus<br>Cazic Thule<br>What do you mean being lazy is no way to live?</td></tr>
